{
  "texts": [
    "Since bypassing rationality understood as appealing to emotion is neither necessary nor sufficient for manipulation, it is unlikely that 'emotional' words or text patterns are reliable indicators of manipulative influence.",
    "Thanks to an anonymous referee for prompting me to clarify the non-intentional use-case.",
    "Noggle (2020) revises the account to focus on the intention to induce a mistake in the victim, mainly to accommodate a problem with false negatives in the trickery account regarding cases of pressure manipulation.",
    "I'd like to draw attention to two different types of cases that might lead to false negatives, and in these cases the observations about the trickery account apply to the revised mistake",
    "Thanks to an anonymous referee for prompting me to clarify the relevance of future use cases."
  ]
}